1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Ever seen a foam explosion that looks like giant toothpaste?

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:05,200
It’s all chemistry!

3
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:07,200
This is called elephant toothpaste.

4
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:12,800
It uses hydrogen peroxide, a catalyst, and dish soap to create a foamy eruption.

5
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:15,600
When hydrogen peroxide decomposes, it releases oxygen.

6
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:18,000
That’s what inflates the soap foam!

7
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:19,600
Look at this tower!

8
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:23,200
It’s a fun demonstration seen in science museums worldwide.

9
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:24,800
But remember, safety first!

10
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:28,000
Always have adult supervision when using concentrated peroxide.

11
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,600
Want more amazing science?

12
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:32,000
Follow for more experiments like this!
